<div xmlns:perseus="http://www.perseus.org/meta/perseus.rdfs#" xmlns:dctype="http://purl.org/dc/dcmitype/" xmlns:tufts="http://www.tufts.edu/" xmlns:alph="http://alpheios.net/namespaces/tei" class="alpheios-lex-text_container en">
    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n3158" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἔνθα</span></b> : I. demonstr.,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">there, thither, then;</span> of place, usually denoting
          rest, <i><span class="en">Il. 1.536</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od. 3.365</span></i>; less often direction, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἔνθ᾽ ἐλθών,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Il. 13.23</span></i>; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc"> ἔνθα
            καὶ ἔνθα</span>, ‘here and there,’ ‘to and fro,’ ‘in length and
          breadth,’ <i><span class="en">Il. 2.476</span></i>, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">462,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Od. 2.213</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il. 7.156</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od. 10.517</span></i>;
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc"> ἢ ἔνθ᾽ ἢ ἔνθα κίοντα</span>, ‘going or
          coming,’ <i><span class="en">Od. 10.574</span></i>; often temporal,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">thereupon</span>, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἔνθα
            ἔπειτα,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Od. 10.297</span></i>; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">
            ἔνθ᾽ αὖ</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 5.1</span></i>;
          introducing apodosis, <i><span class="en">Il. 2.308</span></i>.— II.
          relative, <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">where</span>, <i><span class="en">Il.
            1.610</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; ἔνθ᾽ ἄρα,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Od. 22.335</span></i>; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">
            ἔνθα περ,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Od. 13.284</span></i>; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">
            ἔνθα τε, ν 107</span>, <i><span class="en">Il.
          2.594</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
